<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99658638328393></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99658638328393><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=?item=6414&mid=99658638328393>Further thought</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=60036><span id= >Apallohadas</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>119 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jul 31st 9:33 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.17]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Overnight, I thought about this item more. It's an "OK" item that fell short of being a "Great!" item by one thing. The fact that it's expendable. (Having 2 charges is rather lame as well.)<br><br>IMO, this is another item where the risk does NOT equal the reward. Ever accidentally use a charge on an item while trying to look at it? Would be a sad moment to lose this to a buggy mouse or lag.<br><br>Anyway, (I'm praying that the item developing guys at VI read this) treat items like this just like the donal armor. Don't give them charges, instead make the casting time sufficiently long that the item won't be abused. I think that would go a long way towards balancing risk and reward.<br>&nbsp;<br>High Priest of Povar</td></tr>
